    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>With Nader In, G.O.P. Dreams May Come True</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Julia Weinstein letter comments on some major differences in agendas of Republican and Democratic parties in light of Ralph Nader's claim to finding little difference between the two (July 4 letter)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Why I'm Running: The Nader Critique'' (letter, July 4):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Why I'm Running: The Nader Critique'' (letter, July 4):</p>
        <p>Ralph Nader, defending his role as a third-party candidate, claims to find little difference between the Democrats and the Republicans. Granted that in economic matters, about which even economists cannot agree, there may be little difference, but I would like to point out some major differences in other areas.</p>
        <p>The Republicans are supported by a reactionary right wing seeking to turn back Roe v. Wade and introduce religion into the schools; they support the bearing of arms by anybody and everybody, and oppose one of the foundations of our democracy: separation of church and state.</p>
        <p>JULIA WEINSTEIN  New York, July 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
